<h1>Script: dbcontent-element</h1>
<p>
    A dbcontent element tells where the module shall search for its content.
    The template of the module must have a processing instructions (PI) of type
    importdb, see: <?_wxt xlink id="ImportDB"?>
    to realize the actual extraction of content.
</p>
<p>
  A Module may contain 1 DBContent element,
 </p>
<pre class="prettyprint lang"><![CDATA[  <dbcontent connection="" />]]>
</pre>

<table cellpadding="10px">
  <tr>
    <td  style="vertical-align:top"><strong>connection</strong>(mandatory)</td>
    <td>A complete connectionstring.
    </td>
  </tr>

  <!--
  <tr>
    <td  style="vertical-align:top"><strong>id</strong>(optional)</td>
    <td>An id that identifies this  textcontent in 
    importdb in a template.
    </td>
  </tr>  
  -->
  
  </table>


<p>A dbcontent element may not  contain any elements
</p>


<p>Examples:</p>
<pre class="prettyprint lang"><![CDATA[  <dbcontent connection="jdbc:mysql://a.b.no/vin?user=student&password=student" />]]>
</pre>


</body>
</html>
